STATEMENT: >>>
Semantic parent conversion and final episodic merge shall be bounded by episodic_memory.max_total_records; the current baseline is 3.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-EPISODIC-LIVE-BODY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Live Record Candidate Enrichment
STATEMENT: >>>
When a selected parent record is present in MemoryManager.records, candidate content shall be enriched from the live MemoryRecord full view.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-EPISODIC-FILE-BODY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Indexed Record Candidate Fallback
STATEMENT: >>>
When a selected parent is absent from live RAM, MemoryRetriever shall attempt SQLite/.ragmem reconstruction for that record_id within the active file.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-EPISODIC-MERGE-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Gold-First Episodic Merge
STATEMENT: >>>
Final episodic merging shall process deterministic Gold candidates before semantic episodic candidates.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-EPISODIC-DEDUPE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Episodic Record Deduplication
STATEMENT: >>>
Final episodic merging shall remove duplicate record_id values while preserving the Gold-first source order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-EPISODIC-SOURCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Episodic Source Annotation
STATEMENT: >>>
Merged episodic candidates shall carry episodic_source equal to gold or semantic according to the selected path.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-WORKING-ENRICH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Working Candidate Live Enrichment
STATEMENT: >>>
Working-memory candidates shall be overlaid with current live MemoryRecord content and episode-distance metadata when matching live records exist.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-GOLD-ENRICH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Gold Candidate Live Enrichment
STATEMENT: >>>
Gold candidates shall be overlaid with current live MemoryRecord content and episode-distance metadata when matching live records exist.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-DIRECT-ENRICH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Direct Recall Live Enrichment
STATEMENT: >>>
A Direct Recall candidate shall be overlaid with current live MemoryRecord content when the selected record belongs to the active in-memory record set.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 13. MemoryContextPack Contract

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack preserves raw candidate classes, final synthesis, and diagnostics in one run-local object.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: MemoryContextPack Runtime Container
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryRetriever shall construct one MemoryContextPack for each non-skipped or explicit-empty memory retrieval result.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-WORKING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Working Candidate List
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall maintain working_memory_candidates as an ordered list.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-EPISODIC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Episodic Candidate List
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall maintain episodic_candidates as an ordered list.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-SEMANTIC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Semantic Chunk List
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall maintain semantic_memory_chunks as an ordered list.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-DIRECT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Direct Recall Candidate
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall maintain zero or one direct_recall_candidate.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-CONTEXT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Synthesized Memory Context
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall maintain synthesized_memory_context and memory_synthesis_diagnostics.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-SELECTION-DIAG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Selection Diagnostics
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall maintain selection_diagnostics explaining query, counts, and scoring policy or explicit empty reason.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-TOKEN-REPORT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Token Budget Report
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall maintain a token_budget_report whose current raw-memory estimate is max(1, len(serialized pack) divided by 4).
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-TOKEN-APPROX
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Approximate Token Report
STATEMENT: >>>
The current len(json)//4 estimate shall be identified as rough diagnostics rather than exact provider tokenization.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-TOKEN-REPORT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-COUNTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Candidate Counts
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack.counts shall report list lengths and binary presence of Direct Recall and synthesized context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-DICT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Pack Dictionary Projection
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack.to_dict shall project all candidate groups, synthesis fields, diagnostics, token report, and counts.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-DEBUG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Raw Debug Markdown
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack may render raw candidates and diagnostics as developer debug Markdown, explicitly labeled as not final prompt context.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-NO-DURABLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Pack Non-Persistence
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryContextPack shall remain run-local and shall not be written into durable MemoryRecord files or SQLite truth.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 14. SuperPrompt Write-Back and Controller Integration

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The current controller calls document retrieval first and then the memory path; memory artifacts remain separate from document artifacts.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONTROLLER-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: MemoryRetriever Configuration
STATEMENT: >>>
AppController.configure_memory_retrieval shall construct MemoryRetriever after MemoryManager and MemoryVectorStore exist and shall pass the controller memory SQLite path and runtime configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONTROLLER-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Retrieval Call Order
STATEMENT: >>>
AppController.run_retrieval shall run document Retriever first and then call MemoryRetriever when configured.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONTROLLER-FAILURE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Controller Memory Retrieval Failure Isolation
STATEMENT: >>>
An exception from MemoryRetriever during AppController.run_retrieval shall be logged and shall not erase the already produced document retrieval result.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONTROLLER-NOT-CONFIGURED
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Unconfigured MemoryRetriever
STATEMENT: >>>
When MemoryRetriever is not configured, the controller shall skip memory retrieval and return the SuperPrompt after document retrieval.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-SP-PACK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SuperPrompt Memory Pack
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryRetriever shall assign the MemoryContextPack object to SuperPrompt.memory_context_pack.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-SP-CONTEXT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SuperPrompt Memory Context
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryRetriever shall assign synthesized_memory_context to SuperPrompt.memory_context_text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-SP-BRIEF
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SuperPrompt Active Memory Brief
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryRetriever shall assign the latest eligible ActiveBrief title and body to SuperPrompt.active_memory_brief_title and active_memory_brief.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-SP-EXTRAS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SuperPrompt Memory Extras
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryRetriever shall store pack dictionary, memory context text, debug Markdown, counts, and ActiveBrief title/body in SuperPrompt.extras under current memory keys.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-SP-NO-DOCUMENT-OVERWRITE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Artifact Preservation
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory write-back shall not overwrite base_context_chunks, document retrieval/reranking/A3/A4 views, final_selection_ids, or S_CTX_MD.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-SP-NO-STAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Stage Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Current MemoryRetriever write-back shall not independently replace the SuperPrompt document-stage lifecycle label or document stage history.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-EMPTY-PACK-WRITE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty Pack Write-Back
STATEMENT: >>>
For missing file_id or empty query, MemoryRetriever shall write an empty pack and latest eligible ActiveBrief snapshot into SuperPrompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-NORMAL-PREVIEW
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Normal Preview Uses Synthesized Context
STATEMENT: >>>
The normal SuperPrompt projector shall render memory_context_text and shall not render raw memory candidate debug Markdown by default.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 15. Configuration Governance and Current Consumption

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The memory_retrieval JSON section defines multiple policies, but only fields read by the current implementation shall be treated as effective.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Memory Retrieval Configuration
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory retrieval settings shall be loaded from the versioned runtime_config.json memory_retrieval section.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-PARENT-WEIGHTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Consumed Parent Score Weights
STATEMENT: >>>
Current MemoryScorer shall consume parent_score_weights for QA, Q, and A modes.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-WORKING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Consumed Working Settings
STATEMENT: >>>
Current working-memory lookup shall consume enabled, max_pairs, and exclude_tags.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-EPISODIC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Consumed Episodic Settings
STATEMENT: >>>
Current episodic processing shall consume enabled, max_total_records, max_gold_records, Green semantic/recency weights, Green half-life, recency_enabled, and exclude_tags.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-DIRECT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Consumed Direct Recall Settings
STATEMENT: >>>
Current Direct Recall shall consume enabled and exclude_tags; its current interface inherently returns at most one key match.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-SEMANTIC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Consumed Semantic Chunk Settings
STATEMENT: >>>
Current semantic processing shall consume enabled, max_memory_chunks, semantic/recency weights, half-life, recency_enabled, and exclude_tags.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-TOKEN-LIMITS-NOT-ENFORCED
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Retrieval Token Fields Not Enforced Here
STATEMENT: >>>
The current retrieval path shall not claim enforcement of working-memory, Gold, Green, or Direct Recall max-token fields merely because they exist in runtime_config.json.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-GOLD-BOOLEAN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Gold Bypass Configuration Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
Current Gold recency bypass is implemented by scoring logic; the separate gold_bypass_recency JSON fields shall not be claimed as dynamically controlling that behavior unless the implementation reads them.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-TAG-CATALOG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Tag Catalog Configuration Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryManager currently defines its tag catalog in Python; runtime_config.memory_retrieval.tag_catalog shall not be claimed as the active catalog source until it is consumed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-MIGRATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Operational Parameter Migration
STATEMENT: >>>
Chunking values, raw-hit expansion, collection/model startup values, and remaining retrieval limits shall migrate to validated versioned JSON before being reported as centrally configured.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 16. Error Handling, Security, and Quality Boundaries

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory retrieval must fail or empty safely without fabricating context or weakening history scope.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-NO-FABRICATED-HIT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Fabricated Vector Hit
STATEMENT: >>>
Missing vector collection, embedder, SQLite row, .ragmem body, or live record shall produce missing/empty candidate data rather than invented content.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-RETRIEVAL-FAIL-TRUTH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Failure and Durable Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
A memory retrieval failure shall not modify .ragmem, .ragmeta.json, SQLite record truth, or stored memory vectors.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-INGEST-FAIL-TRUTH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Ingestion Failure and Durable Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
A memory ingestion failure shall leave the durable MemoryRecord body and current metadata intact.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-NO-CROSS-HISTORY-AUTO
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Unapproved Automatic Cross-History Retrieval
STATEMENT: >>>
Automatic working, Gold, semantic parent, and semantic chunk retrieval shall remain active-history scoped; only exact Direct Recall may cross histories in the current design.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-NO-SECRET
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Secret Vector Metadata
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory vector documents and metadata shall not intentionally include provider API keys or browser credentials.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-PUBLIC-LOG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Public Retrieval Logging
STATEMENT: >>>
Public logs shall report compact counts and statuses and shall not expose complete memory bodies, query embeddings, or vector values by default.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIDENTIAL-LOG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Confidential Retrieval Diagnostics
STATEMENT: >>>
Complete raw hits, candidates, scoring snapshots, and pack payloads shall remain behind explicitly enabled confidential developer logging.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-SCORE-REPRODUCIBILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Scoring Reproducibility
STATEMENT: >>>
Diagnostics shall preserve effective scoring policy, candidate counts, query text, and active file identity sufficiently to reproduce selection decisions without exposing credentials.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-DETERMINISTIC-TESTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Deterministic Retrieval Testability
STATEMENT: >>>
Vector ID generation, chunk splitting, metadata sanitation, distance conversion, role aggregation, recency decay, tag filtering, deterministic lookups, candidate merge, and pack projection shall be independently testable.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-NO-DOC-A3
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Memory-to-Document A3 Claim
STATEMENT: >>>
Memory semantic chunks shall not be marked with document A3ChunkStatus or inserted into document A3/A4 stage views in the current implementation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 17. Traceability and Acceptance Criteria

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
These criteria verify derivative memory ingestion, retrieval, candidate selection, and SuperPrompt handoff.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-CODE-OWNERSHIP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Ingestion and Retrieval Code Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
MemoryChunker, MemoryIngestionManager, MemoryVectorStore, MemoryRetriever, MemoryIndexLookup, MemoryScorer, and MemoryContextPack shall map to the deepest applicable UIDs in this document.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-SIBLING-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sibling Ownership Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Durable recording/files shall remain owned by 51; ActiveBrief algorithms, runtime compression, and synthesis shall remain owned by 53.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-ENTRIES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Vector Entry Roles
STATEMENT: >>>
Given one non-empty MemoryRecord, ingestion shall create one non-empty record handle and the expected ordered non-empty question and answer entries with stable traceable IDs.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ENTRY-ROLES

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-IDEMPOTENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Record Re-Ingestion
STATEMENT: >>>
Re-ingesting the same record_id shall replace prior vectors and shall not increase the number of duplicate IDs for that record.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-IDEMPOTENT-REPRESENTATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-ASYNC-FAIL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Ingestion Failure Isolation
STATEMENT: >>>
If vector embedding or replacement fails, the corresponding .ragmem block and metadata shall remain available as durable truth.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-INGEST-FAIL-TRUTH

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-WORKING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Working Memory
STATEMENT: >>>
Given an active history with more records than max_pairs, working lookup shall return only the latest configured non-excluded records from that history.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-WORKING-LATEST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-DIRECT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Exact Direct Recall
STATEMENT: >>>
Given the same Direct Recall Key in multiple histories, lookup shall return at most one non-excluded result using tag priority and recency ordering.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-DIRECT-PRIORITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-PARENT-SCORE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Parent Role Scoring
STATEMENT: >>>
Given multiple hits for one parent and role, the current parent role score shall equal the maximum role hit and final semantic score shall apply the configured QA/Q/A weights.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-ROLE-MAX

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-RECENCY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Episode Recency
STATEMENT: >>>
For Green records at k zero and k equal to half-life, recency scores shall be 1.0 and 0.5 before semantic/recency weighted combination.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-RECENCY-HALF-LIFE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-GOLD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Gold Priority and Deduplication
STATEMENT: >>>
A Gold record also selected semantically shall appear once in final episodic candidates and shall retain Gold-first source priority.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-EPISODIC-DEDUPE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-SEMANTIC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Semantic Chunk Roles
STATEMENT: >>>
Final semantic memory chunks shall contain question/answer evidence only and shall exclude record_handle entries.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-SEMANTIC-ROLES

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-SCOPE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Automatic History Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
Automatic semantic and deterministic retrieval shall not return a record from another history solely because the active-file filter failed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-FILTER-FAILURE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-PACK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: MemoryContextPack
STATEMENT: >>>
After one successful memory retrieval, the SuperPrompt shall contain a MemoryContextPack whose candidate counts match its actual lists and optional Direct Recall/context fields.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-PACK-COUNTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-SEPARATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Document Artifact Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
Running memory retrieval shall leave document chunk objects, stage views, and S_CTX_MD unchanged.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-SP-NO-DOCUMENT-OVERWRITE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-PERMISSION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Memory Context Permission
STATEMENT: >>>
When PreProcessing sets allow_memory_context false, the final SuperPrompt shall not receive synthesized memory context for that request.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-MEMORY-PERMISSION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Configuration Consumption Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
Changing an unconsumed JSON field shall not be represented as changing runtime behavior; changing a consumed field shall be observable in selection or diagnostics.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CONFIG-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-MEM-IR-AC-SYNC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Requirement-Code Synchronization
STATEMENT: >>>
A memory ingestion/retrieval baseline shall not be accepted when vector identity, history scope, scoring equations, tag policy, candidate roles, pack semantics, or configuration authority contradicts this document.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-MEM-IR-CODE-OWNERSHIP

[[/SECTION]]
